Rakuen's interest in the Flood Court Remnants is both engineering and legal. On the engineering
side, the Court's records of Khardaan's hydraulic pressure management during flood conditions
are a historical precedent for root-weave flood-routing architecture—the vegetative adaptation
of principles the Flood Court enforced mechanically. The Garden Ledger Clerks' flood architecture
records include a cross-reference to Flood Court pressure calibration standards as a historical
ancestor. On the legal side, the Court's water-right adjudication records predate Rakuen's
founding and potentially establish precedents relevant to Rakuen's water access disputes with
Midgaard's administrative framework during the ashfall emergency periods. The Clerks have not
yet succeeded in consulting the surviving spirits through the Court's judicial protocol, but
the formal inquiry has been filed with Khardaan's Spring Wardens.

