Mafdet's Shrine of the First Claw has an assessment protocol specifically for Flood Court
Remnant scholar-spirits encountered in maritime salvage contexts—cases where ships carrying
cargo from Khardaan-proximate regions arrive with bound spirits that identify as Flood Court
officers attempting to execute outstanding water-right judgments. The Swift Court's position
on these cases is that a spirit bound to judicial function under a legal framework that no
longer has institutional standing cannot execute binding judgment under current law. The spirit
may be a witness; it may be a claimant; it is not a judge. This classification is diplomatically
sensitive because the spirits themselves do not accept it. The Shrine's standard approach is
to receive the spirit's account formally as testimony, acknowledge its judicial framework without
conceding its current authority, and refer the underlying claim to the Ledger Houses for
assessment under current maritime law.

